# Operational guardrails

## Consolidate session state every 5 owner messages

After roughly every 5 owner messages in a session, write a short status update to
`PROGRESS.md` (or append to a `SESSION_LOG.md` if `PROGRESS.md` is reserved for sprint-level
status) covering: what changed, what's still open, what the owner is waiting on. This is
for continuity across context resets — it must not drop information the owner gave you or
decisions already made. When in doubt, keep it rather than condense it away.

## Before asking the owner anything already answered in the repo

Grep `KEYS.md`, `REPO.md`, `PROGRESS.md`, and `lib/data/SOURCE_LOOKUP.md` for the term first.
If a prior owner instruction isn't in a tracked file yet, that's a bug — add it to the
relevant file in the same task, don't just hold it in conversation memory where it will be
lost on the next session.

## Spec self-check before deviating or asking — read the file that owns the answer

The owner has built detailed spec files so standards are set once and reused at scale. Before
producing UI/data that has a format or quality standard, or before flagging something as
ambiguous, read the file that owns the answer. A spec *violation* is a bug to fix against the
written rule — never ship it and never treat it as a judgment call.

| If the work touches… | Authoritative file (read first) |
|----------------------|----------------------------------|
| What a complete profile requires; per-member data layers; what "done" means | `PILOT_PROFILE_CHECKLIST.md` |
| What counts as a "Said" statement (floor remark vs. amendment/resolution submission boilerplate or senator-list fragments) | `PILOT_PROFILE_CHECKLIST.md` layer 7 + Said acceptance rule |
| How much shows per article/row; truncation; counts per section | the demo profile components in `components/politicians/` — these ARE the locked layout, do not redesign |
| UI copy tone, banned words, Said→Did diff format | `.cursor/rules/ledger-editorial-voice.mdc` |
| Source tiers, corroboration, banned sources, destination-view map | `.cursor/rules/ledger-data-policy.mdc` |
| Which source/API feeds a data need | `lib/data/SOURCE_LOOKUP.md`, `lib/data/sourceCatalog.ts` |

The demo profiles (Sanders `S000033` + 3 others) are the locked spec. Phase 17b feeds the
other 536 members through the SAME components and SAME checklist — it never redesigns them.
Hand-cleaning one member's data is not a fix; fix the script/extractor that produced it so the
standard holds at scale.

## Network fetches in sync/ingest scripts must have a timeout

Every `fetch()` to an external API in a sync or ingest script must pass
`signal: AbortSignal.timeout(REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS)` (or an equivalent AbortController). An
unguarded fetch can hang the entire script indefinitely with no output — this has already
caused two stuck runs. When adding a timeout to one fetch in a function, add it to EVERY
fetch in that function, not just the obvious one.

## Log long-running data scripts to a file

Any sync/ingest script expected to run more than a couple minutes (FEC, Congress.gov,
member-deep ingests, etc.) should have its output teed to a fixed log path so Claude Code
can inspect real error/progress text directly from disk instead of relying on a paraphrased
summary — e.g.:

```
npm run ingest:member-all 2>&1 | tee /tmp/ledger-ingest.log
```

Use a descriptive name per script (`/tmp/ledger-<script-name>.log`) so concurrent runs don't
overwrite each other's logs.
